---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../components/Breadcrumb.astro';

const title = 'Privacy Policy';
const description = 'How DrugText.org handles privacy. We do not require accounts, do not run third-party ad trackers, and minimize data collection by default.';
const updated = '2026-06-07';

const jsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'WebPage',
  name: 'Privacy Policy',
  url: 'https://www.drugtext.org/privacy',
  description,
  dateModified: updated,
};
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} jsonLd={jsonLd}>
  <article class="page">
    <Breadcrumb items={[{ label: 'Home', href: '/' }, { label: 'Privacy' }]} />

    <header class="page__head">
      <h1 class="dt-h1">PRIVACY_POLICY</h1>
      <p class="page__lede">Last updated: <time datetime={updated}>{updated}</time></p>
    </header>

    <div class="dt-prose">
      <p>DrugText.org is built around the assumption that visitors are entitled to read harm-reduction information privately. This policy explains, in plain language, what data we collect, why, and what we do not do.</p>

      <h2>1. What we do not do</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>We do not require an account to read any public page on the Site.</li>
        <li>We do not run third-party advertising trackers.</li>
        <li>We do not sell, rent, or share personal data with data brokers.</li>
        <li>We do not fingerprint visitors for cross-site identification.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. What we collect</h2>
      <p>By default we collect only what is needed to operate and protect the Site:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Server access logs</strong>: request URL, timestamp, response code, user-agent, and a truncated IP address. Used for abuse mitigation and capacity planning. Retained for a short window, then deleted or aggregated.</li>
        <li><strong>Anonymous analytics</strong>: page view counts, referrer, and approximate country, aggregated and not linked to individual visitors.</li>
        <li><strong>Submissions you send us</strong>: if you email a correction, submit a research contribution, or send a brand tip, we receive the contents of that message and the email address you sent it from. We use it to act on the submission and to follow up if needed.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. Cookies and storage</h2>
      <p>We use a minimal set of first-party cookies and localStorage entries to remember interface preferences (such as a chosen filter view on the peptides index). We do not use cookies for behavioural advertising. You can clear them at any time through your browser's settings.</p>

      <h2>4. Third-party content</h2>
      <p>Some pages embed fonts or other static assets served from a third-party CDN. Those providers may receive standard request metadata (IP, user-agent) when your browser fetches the asset. We do not share additional information with them.</p>

      <h2>5. Sponsors and brand reviews</h2>
      <p>Sponsor logos shown on the Site are paid placements and are marked accordingly. Brand review content is editorial and is not influenced by sponsorship. We do not share visitor data with sponsors.</p>

      <h2>6. Children</h2>
      <p>The Site is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe a child has sent us information, contact us so we can delete it.</p>

      <h2>7. Your rights</h2>
      <p>Depending on where you live, you may have the right to request access to, correction of, or deletion of personal data we hold about you (typically the contents of an email you sent us). You may exercise these rights via the <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.</p>

      <h2>8. Security</h2>
      <p>We apply reasonable administrative and technical safeguards to the limited data we hold. No system is perfectly secure; we do not guarantee that data in transit or at rest is immune to interception or unauthorized access.</p>

      <h2>9. Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this policy as practices change. The "Last updated" date at the top reflects the most recent change.</p>

      <h2>10. Contact</h2>
      <p>Privacy questions can be sent through the <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page { max-width: 880px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 40px 48px 80px; }
  .page__head { margin: 28px 0 40px; }
  .page__lede {
    font-family: var(--dt-font-mono);
    font-size: 13px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: var(--dt-text-muted);
    margin: 14px 0 0;
  }
  @media (max-width: 720px) { .page { padding: 32px 24px 64px; } }
</style>
